  - Keep the pre-build cleanup for stale `win-unpacked`.
  - Add a Windows-only retry around the electron-builder Step 5 command, so transient exe locks during electron-builder resource editing cause a clean rebuild attempt instead of changing packaging semantics.
- Code changes:
  - Removed `win.asar: false` from `clipper_electron/electron-builder.yml`.
  - Updated `clipper_electron/scripts/build-app.mjs` so `runElectronBuilder()` retries Step 5 up to 3 times on Windows, cleaning `dist-app/win-unpacked` before retry attempts.
- Verification:
  - GREEN: `node --check scripts/build-app.mjs`.
  - GREEN: `git -C clipper_electron diff --check`.

